topic: Companies Workflow Series ("Economy of EU States")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for obtaining the type, legal form, and industry of a company
goals.2: Identify the BGP to retrieve all companies owned by a company located in a EU country
goals.3: Which company has the largest presence in E.U.?
goals.4: Companies have different 'legal forms', compare the number of companies divided in different legal forms
goals.5: Analyze the number of companies per type, legal form, and industry in each state
goals.5.1: What are the top-3 legal form in E.U.?
goals.5.2: For which companies is defined some form of income or market capitalization or total assets? What is the min, max, and average in each country for a given legal form?
goals.5.3: Which business in each country owns more businesses in other E.U. countries?
goals.5.4: What can we say about industry sectors in various countries?

5.3.narrative: Count the number of businesses owned by another business in different country and then for each country I extract the max value
5.3.query: SELECT ?cname (MAX(?num) AS ?max) WHERE { ?com wdt:P31 ?type ; wdt:P17 ?cou . ?cou wdt:P463 wd:Q458 . FILTER(?com = ?c). { SELECT ?c (COUNT(DISTINCT ?sub) AS ?num) WHERE { ?c wdt:P31 ?type ; wdt:P17 ?country ; (wdt:P1830)* ?sub . ?sub wdt:P31 ?type ; wdt:P17 ?country2 . ?country wdt:P463 wd:Q458 . ?country2 wdt:P463 wd:Q458 . FILTER(?type = wd:Q4830453). FILTER(?country != ?country2) . } GROUP BY ?c } ?com <http://schema.org/name> ?company . ?cou <http://schema.org/name> ?cname . } GROUP BY ?cname ORDER BY DESC (?max)
